case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_circumstances:
This is a Dekalb County Police Department case, assisted by the NCMEC.  Tips/leads can be submitted to NCMEC or to the Dekalb County PD at 770-724-7890.

The skeletal remains of this decedent were found behind a building on Ranchwood Drive, near Lavista Road and I-285 in northern Dekalb County, GA.  The decedent is estimated to have been 5'-04" to 5'07" and 115 to 140 pounds in life.
case_head_hair: The decedent had long, curly hair which appeared to be light brown in color.  Her hair had a "frosted" appearance.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body: The decedent was wearing a black t-shirt with an inside collar label reading "KLM Dome" (size large) and a multi-colored design/logo on the front reading "WAIKOLOA".  She was also wearing blue denim jeans.
case_footwear: The decedent was wearing white cross-training type shoes with blue and red stripes (size 8).  The sole of the left shoe is marked XJ900, size 8.
